source.name: Adoption of Genetically Engineered Crops in the U.S.
source.description: This data product summarizes the extent of adoption of herbicide-tolerant and insect-resistant genetically engineered crops in the United States. Data cover GE varieties of corn, cotton, and soybeans over the 2000-2012 period, by State.
